Yes. Add both in **Arthur Core**.

## 1. Redis TTL config in properties

### `application.yml`

```yaml
arthur:
  session:
    ttl-minutes: 60
  handoff:
    ttl-seconds: 60
  auth-transaction:
    ttl-minutes: 5
```

## 2. Create properties class

**Location:** `config/ArthurSecurityProperties.java`

```java
@Data
@Configuration
@ConfigurationProperties(prefix = "arthur")
public class ArthurSecurityProperties {

    private Session session = new Session();
    private Handoff handoff = new Handoff();
    private AuthTransaction authTransaction = new AuthTransaction();

    @Data
    public static class Session {
        private long ttlMinutes = 60;
    }

    @Data
    public static class Handoff {
        private long ttlSeconds = 60;
    }

    @Data
    public static class AuthTransaction {
        private long ttlMinutes = 5;
    }
}
```

Make sure configuration properties scan is enabled. In main app:

```java
@ConfigurationPropertiesScan
@SpringBootApplication
public class ArthurCoreApplication {
}
```

## 3. Update `RedisSessionService`

```java
@Service
@RequiredArgsConstructor
@Slf4j
public class RedisSessionService {

    private static final String PREFIX = "session:";

    private final RedisTemplate<String, Object> redisTemplate;
    private final ObjectMapper objectMapper;
    private final ArthurSecurityProperties properties;

    public void save(UserSession session) {
        redisTemplate.opsForValue().set(
                PREFIX + session.getSessionId(),
                session,
                Duration.ofMinutes(properties.getSession().getTtlMinutes())
        );

        log.debug(
                "Arthur session saved for userId={}, appId={}, selectedSalesPoint={}",
                session.getUserId(),
                session.getAppId(),
                session.getSelectedSalesPointId()
        );
    }

    public UserSession findBySessionId(String sessionId) {
        Object value = redisTemplate.opsForValue().get(PREFIX + sessionId);

        if (value == null) {
            return null;
        }

        if (value instanceof UserSession session) {
            return session;
        }

        return objectMapper.convertValue(value, UserSession.class);
    }
}
```

## 4. Update `RedisLoginHandoffService`

```java
@Service
@RequiredArgsConstructor
@Slf4j
public class RedisLoginHandoffService {

    private static final String PREFIX = "handoff:";

    private final RedisTemplate<String, Object> redisTemplate;
    private final ObjectMapper objectMapper;
    private final ArthurSecurityProperties properties;

    public void save(LoginHandoff handoff) {
        redisTemplate.opsForValue().set(
                PREFIX + handoff.getCode(),
                handoff,
                Duration.ofSeconds(properties.getHandoff().getTtlSeconds())
        );

        log.info("Login handoff saved for appId={}", handoff.getAppId());
    }
}
```

Also update auth transaction TTL similarly wherever you save state/PKCE.

