# CSRF protection

## 5. Add/Update `SecurityConfig`

**Location:** `config/SecurityConfig.java`

```java
@Configuration
@EnableWebSecurity
public class SecurityConfig {

    @Bean
    public SecurityFilterChain securityFilterChain(HttpSecurity http) throws Exception {
        http
                .csrf(csrf -> csrf
                        .ignoringRequestMatchers(
                                "/auth/start",
                                "/auth/handoff/exchange"
                        )
                )
                .authorizeHttpRequests(auth -> auth
                        .requestMatchers("/auth/**").permitAll()
                        .requestMatchers("/sales-points/**").permitAll()
                        .anyRequest().permitAll()
                );

        return http.build();
    }
}
```

Why ignore those:

* `/auth/start` may be AJAX from login page
* `/auth/handoff/exchange` is server-to-server from B2Boost
* `/sales-points/select` should keep CSRF enabled because it is browser form POST

## 6. Add CSRF token to Thymeleaf form

**Location:** `templates/views/sales-points.html`

Inside the form:

```html
<form method="post" th:action="@{/sales-points/select}">
    <input type="hidden"
           th:name="${_csrf.parameterName}"
           th:value="${_csrf.token}" />

    <input type="hidden" name="appId" th:value="${appId}">

    <div th:each="sp : ${salesPoints}">
        <label>
            <input type="radio" name="salesPointId" th:value="${sp.id}" required>
            <span th:text="${sp.label}">Sales Point</span>
        </label>
        <br>
    </div>

    <button type="submit">Confirm</button>
</form>
```

That’s it.

